GIT COMMANDS â€“ QUICK NOTES
ğŸ”¹ 1. Git Setup / Repo Start

Initialize new git repo:git init

Connect project to GitHub:git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git

Check remote connection:git remote -v
ğŸ”¹ 2. Daily Workflow (Most Important ğŸš€)

Check changed files:git status

Add all files:git add .

Add specific file:

git add filename.java

Commit (local save):

git commit -m "your message"

Push to GitHub:

git push

Pull latest changes:

git pull
ğŸ”¹ 3. First Time Push (Upstream Set)

If error: no upstream branch

git push -u origin main

After that only:

git push
ğŸ”¹ 4. Branch Commands âš¡

Check current branch:

git branch

Create new branch:

git branch feature1

Switch branch:

git checkout feature1

OR (modern way):

git switch feature1

Create + switch together:

git checkout -b feature1
ğŸ”¹ 5. History Commands

See commit history:

git log

Short log:

git log --oneline

See changes:

git diff
ğŸ”¹ 6. Undo / Fix Mistakes âš ï¸

Edit last commit message:

git commit --amend

Unstage file:

git restore --staged filename.java

Delete last commit (danger):

git reset --hard HEAD~1
ğŸ”¥ Standard Daily Workflow (Placement Ready)
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Day X practice"
git push